abstract: A Native American tribe's long running effort to secure sovereign land for a casino in Massachusetts is now in the hands of a federal appeals court in Boston.
snippet: A Native American tribe's long running effort to secure sovereign land for a casino in Massachusetts is now in the hands of a federal appeals court in Boston.
lead_paragraph: BOSTON — A Native American tribe's long running effort to secure sovereign land for a casino in Massachusetts is now in the hands of a federal appeals court in Boston.
headline_main: Appeals Court Weighs Tribe’s Quest for Casino Land
headline_print_headline: Appeals Court Weighs Tribe’s Quest for Casino Land

abstract: Billionaire presidential candidate and former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg snagged his first gubernatorial endorsement Wednesday, as Rhode Island Gov. Gina Raimondo called him the right leader to take on President Donald Trump.
snippet: Billionaire presidential candidate and former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg snagged his first gubernatorial endorsement Wednesday, as Rhode Island Gov. Gina Raimondo called him the right leader to take on President Donald Trump.
lead_paragraph: PROVIDENCE, R.I. — Billionaire presidential candidate and former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg snagged his first gubernatorial endorsement Wednesday, as Rhode Island Gov. Gina Raimondo called him the right leader to take on President Donald Trump.
headline_main: Rhode Island Governor Backs Michael Bloomberg for President
headline_print_headline: Rhode Island Governor Backs Michael Bloomberg for President

headline_main: State of the Union Address, Impeachment, Iowa: Your Wednesday Briefing

abstract: And Democrats can easily show that the president has done little to help it.
snippet: And Democrats can easily show that the president has done little to help it.
lead_paragraph: Every few days, fresh economic statistics roll out, each one almost invariably reinforcing the perception of a solid economy. In his State of the Union address on Tuesday night, President Trump reinforced that impression — and took credit for it.

abstract: The U.S. prosecution of Mexican politicians for drug trafficking could help President López Obrador fight corruption, but he’s failing to build on it.
snippet: The U.S. prosecution of Mexican politicians for drug trafficking could help President López Obrador fight corruption, but he’s failing to build on it.
lead_paragraph: MEXICO CITY — While the sex-crimes trial of Harvey Weinstein takes center stage, another case is winding through a New York court with shattering implications. Federal prosecutors in Brooklyn are pursuing drug trafficking charges against Genaro García Luna, a key architect of the drug war of former President Felipe Calderón. After Mr. García Luna’s latest hearing on Jan. 21, his lawyer reiterated that he pleas not guilty, saying he “adamantly denies that he accepted any bribes” (from traffickers) and will go to trial.

abstract: The Republican-controlled Senate is expected to acquit President Trump on both charges, drawing a fractious impeachment trial to a close.
snippet: The Republican-controlled Senate is expected to acquit President Trump on both charges, drawing a fractious impeachment trial to a close.
lead_paragraph: What we’re expecting to see: The Senate is set to vote Wednesday on two articles of impeachment against President Trump. The first charges him with abusing the power of his office by pressuring Ukraine to interfere in the 2020 presidential election on his behalf by withholding military aid and a White House meeting; the other charges him with obstructing Congress in a bid to hide his wrongdoing.

headline_main: Impeachment Trial: What to Watch Before the Final Votes

abstract: Impeachment will end in the Senate. It’s time to take up consensus issues.
snippet: Impeachment will end in the Senate. It’s time to take up consensus issues.
lead_paragraph: On Wednesday I will join a majority of my Senate colleagues in opposing the impeachment of President Trump brought by the House of Representatives.
